content:
Creates a detailed summary report when Claude Code completes its work session. Includes statistics on files modified, lines changed, test results, and pending git changes.

```json
{
  "Stop": [
    {
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "echo '📊 === WORKFLOW COMPLETION REPORT ===' && echo '📅 Completed at: '$(date) && echo '📝 Files modified in session:' && git status --short 2>/dev/null | wc -l && echo '✅ Git changes:' && git diff --stat 2>/dev/null || echo 'Not in a git repository' && echo '🧪 Test summary:' && (npm test -- --listTests 2>/dev/null | wc -l | xargs echo 'Test files available:') || echo 'No test framework detected' && echo '📦 Dependencies status:' && (npm outdated 2>/dev/null | head -5 || echo 'Dependencies up to date') && echo '💾 Session data saved to: .claude-session-'$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)'.log' && echo '================================'"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
